The tokenizer migration can permanently leave migrated databases with an empty FTS index after an interrupted or failed open because the repair step is only attempted during the same open that crosses schema version 11.

Review comment:

- [P1] Make tokenizer reindex retryable after migration — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:1691-1692
  If a migrated v10 database crashes or hits a transient error after step 11 commits but before `reproject_search_index_after_tokenizer_upgrade` completes, `user_version` is already 11 and the next open will skip this block, leaving `search_index` empty because the migration dropped and recreated it. This affects existing databases crossing the tokenizer upgrade boundary; gate the re-tokenization on actual index state or persist a separate completion marker so retries repair the FTS table.
